I have the BOS, 2nd edition in front of me, and this is what it says about
building, structure, and room names on page 44:

Capitalize all elements of a building address, including the room name.

Sister Mary Helene

St. Agnes Hospital Emergency Room

Ourtown, USA

Then on page 57, under Capitalization, it says:

In particular, avoid the use of unnecessary or inappropriate capitals. Do
not, for

example, capitalize a common-noun reference to a thing or person if it is
just one

of many other such things or persons. Thus, emergency room and recovery room

are not capitalized. Think of the rule for generic versus brand names for
drugs.

The generic term (common noun) emergency room is applied to all emergency

rooms, so it is not capitalized.

Easyrider

