Well, I hate to break it to you, but what you've always been doing is
what the BOS advocates, page 47 of the second edition.
"departments
Lowercase common nouns designating department names;reserve capitals
for proper nouns or adjectives, in addresses, or when part of a federal
government agency name.
(examples)
She is head of the St. Mary's Hospital surgery department.
He works for the State Department in Washington, DC.
The patient is head of the English department at the local university.

However, capitalize a department name that is referred to as an entity
(doesn't have the word "department" or "unit" or whatever after it).

The patient was referred to Anesthesia for preoperative evaluation.
The report from Pathology indicates that the tumor is benign."

Gisele

--
Gisele
